Script to generate GIBBS input for adsorption isotherms.
Source files are indicated in SOURCE

1- Run python script 'create.py'

The GIBBS input files are:
nt12.opt.cris
sioh.coord
aloh.coord

Other xyz files are generated for visualisation purposes:
    nt12.opt.slice.xyz
corresponds to the data written in nt12.opt.cris from which grids are computed
    nt12.opt.framework.xyz
same with 5 periodic replicas
    nt12.opt.gibbs.xyz
nanotube shifted for visualisation of certain GIBBS configuration files (confs.res)
    nt12.opt.sioh.xyz and nt12.opt.aloh.xyz
show only the adsorbates SiOH and AlOH
